    <briefdescription>
<para>Convex monotone yield-curve interpolation method. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Enhances implementation of the convex monotone method described in &quot;Interpolation Methods for Curve Construction&quot; by Hagan &amp; West AMF Vol 13, No2 2006.</para>
<para>A setting of monotonicity = 1 and quadraticity = 0 will reproduce the basic Hagan/West method. However, this can produce excessive gradients which can mean P&amp;L swings for some curves. Setting monotonicity &lt; 1 and/or quadraticity &gt; 0 produces smoother curves. Extra enhancement to avoid negative values (if required) is in place.</para>
<para><simplesect kind="warning"><para>See the <ref refid="class_quant_lib_1_1_interpolation" kindref="compound">Interpolation</ref> class for information about the required lifetime of the underlying data. </para>
</simplesect>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
